Hi Matthias,

FastInsertOperation could probably be a drop-in replacement for InsertOperation, but unfortunately it is not thread-safe \(it caches information during the execute\(\) call\). You would perform the operation like this:

new FastInsertOperation\(\).execute\(connection, insertDataset\);

The CachedDatabaseOperation works like so:

CachedDatabaseOperation op = new CachedDatabaseOperation\(dataSet, new FastInsertOperation\(\)\);
op.execute\(connection1\);    
...
op.execute\(connection2\);

Note that if dataSet changes, the cached operation will NOT reflect the changes\!\! The CachedDatabaseOperation records all the prepared and batched statements on the first execute\(\), and the StatementPlaybackEngine \(sorry about the name\!\) replays the recorded statements in future execute\(\)s. The dataset is thrown away after the first execute\(\) is completed.

Is this enough information to go on??

